com.google.gxp.compiler.fs
Class InMemoryFileSystem

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gxp.compiler.fs.AbstractFileSystem
      com.google.gxp.compiler.fs.InMemoryFileSystem
All Implemented Interfaces:
FileSystem
public class InMemoryFileSystem
extends AbstractFileSystem

A FileSystem implementation that resides in-memory. This is primarily useful for testing, though it could theoretically be used as a stub FileSystem in other situations. An InMemoryFileSystem starts out empty. Its filename representation is exactly the same as the abstract representation used by FileRef (this is an abstract FileSystem, after all).

A note about timestamps: each instance of InMemoryFileSystem has its own internal "virtual clock" which is initialized to 0 and does not change except via explicit calls to setCurrentTime. When files are created their last modified time will be set to the value of this virtual clock if its value is positive. Files created when the clock has a non-positive value will have an unretrievable last modified time.
